  "title": "Mechanical & Vehicle Maintenance Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform Store receiving, verification of goods receive/Issuing out and storing of goods.</li>\n  <li>Perform Store administrative work</li>\n  <li>Manage storeroom inventory</li>\n  <li>Provide technical support when necessary.</li>\n  <li>Perform basic repair, inspection, reassembly, refitting, and adjusting products as required.</li>\n  <li>Maintain work area clean, safe, and orderly.</li>\n  <li>Servicing &amp; repair landscape equipment / vehicles</li>\n  <li>Service / Maintenance/ Repair of motor vehicles and equipment including engine checks, chassis checks, battery checks and identify mechanical defects or faults and replace defective or worn parts.</li>\n  <li>Carry out component overhaul</li>\n  <li>Carry out fault diagnosis</li>\n  <li>Fundamental electrical knowledge to troubleshoot electrical systems and usuage of Engine Diagnostic Equipment to troubleshoot “Check Engine Light’ to identify electrical faults, perform repairs and replace defective parts.</li>\n  <li>Provide roadside assistance to troubleshoot, identify and rectify faults on spot.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance to health and safety polices and procedures in the course of work inside workshop area at times.</li>\n  <li>Maintain the cleanliness and neatness of the workshop area thru good housekeeping.</li>\n  <li>To perform any other ad hoc tasks assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Relevant working experience highly welcomed</li>\n  <li>Positive attitude, willingness to learn and good team player</li>\n  <li>Candidate must possess at least Primary/Secondary School/\"O\" Level in Others or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 1 Year of working experience in the related field is required for this position.</li>\n  <li>Possess valid Class 2B/ Class 3 and above will be a bonus</li>\n</ul>",
